The fraud and corruption case against former eThekwini mayor, Zandile Gumede has been transferred to the High Court in Durban after a short appearance on Tuesday. #eNCA​ Mreporter Lethiwe Mdluli is following this story. #DStv403 DURBAN - Former eThekwini mayor, Zandile Gumede and her co-accused will be appearing in the High Court in Durban in June. The matter was transferred from the Durban Commercial Crimes Court following a short appearance by the accused on Tuesday morning. READ: Gumede, co-accused to appear in court Gumede and her co-accused are facing charges relating to a R430-million Durban Solid Waste tender, issued in 2017 when she was still mayor. There are a total of 2,786 charges against them.